{"ts":"2026-07-06T23:26:12.453Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/body","value":"pm-a22j records a ONE-TIME token-cost baseline for the before/after consolidation comparison. Nothing prevents the surface from silently regrowing afterwards — the historical growth pattern (each feature adds output, help text, contract entries) will resume unless cost is gated like any other quality budget.\n\nTurn the pm-a22j measurement script into a permanent regression gate:\n- Corpus of representative invocations run against a deterministic fixture workspace (help surfaces, contracts, and the hot agent read path: list/get/context/next/search in default, json, and toon).\n- Byte + approx-token measurement per invocation, compared against a checked-in budget manifest.\n- Gate fails on exceedance; budgets are only raised via an explicit commit that the diff makes visible (same discipline as eslint-suppressions.json max-17 and the LOC cap).\n\nThis makes 'EXTREMELY token-efficient output' an enforced invariant instead of a one-off cleanup, and gives the pm-n7rr consolidation a permanent ratchet: every help/contract shrink it ships becomes the new ceiling."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-cu1i"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"Token-cost regression gate: CI budget check over a representative command-output corpus"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":""},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Task"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":1},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["agent-ux","ci","token-efficiency"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-06T23:26:12.453Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-06T23:26:12.453Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/estimated_minutes","value":240},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"Checked-in budget manifest (bytes + approx tokens) for a representative invocation corpus: pm --help, per-noun help, contracts summary/full, list/get/context/next/search in default+json+toon, MCP tool-list payload; deterministic fixture workspace; gate wired into the CI static-gates job; failure output names the offending command and the delta; budgets change only via an explicit reviewed commit (eslint-suppressions baseline pattern); budget-update procedure documented"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-n7rr"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"low"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":"high"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/dependencies","value":[{"id":"pm-a22j","kind":"blocked_by","created_at":"2026-07-06T23:26:12.453Z"},{"id":"pm-pbyu","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-06T23:26:12.453Z"}]}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"a88c0b1101eaca4735226a2106f6a588c2803b223c190b63dddd1b0e10197173","message":""}
